The paper discusses distributed learning with regularization, which is a common topic in machine learning. The use of least squares regularization in a reproducing kernel Hilbert space (RKHS) suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The divide-and-conquer approach used in the algorithm suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The analysis of error bounds suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the use of integral operator approach suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory).
